snippet.textDisplay: Since you guys are considered as legal age in Canada, why not plan a trip here in your new mobile home. Cross over in Buffalo at the Peace Bridge, visit The Canadian Side of Niagara Falls and do a bit of tourist stuff. Plan for end of June or July when the weather is the nicest. We have plenty of places you can park the van overnight and there are washroom facilities. Don't cross at Niagara itself, as it doesn't seem to have the best reputation (American Side). Just remember guns, pepper spray, or criminal records are not allowed in Canada, most foods are however check via google before you pack. You can also do a round trip and head back to US via Michigan or go to upper pennisula and visit Mackinac Island taking the Mackinac Bridge (longest suspension bridge in western hemisphere and is american).
